revision.text: Possibly: The art of dying well, by Roberto Francesco Romolo Bellarmino. (London : Printed by I. Dalton. The book may be had at Mr. Colstons Sword-Cutler at Charing-Cross, Mr. Jones Stationer by St. Bartholomew's Cloisters, at Mr. Sunderland's Coffee-House in Warwick-Lane, Pilgrim's Coffee-House in High Holborn, near Little Queen-Street, Mrs. White's in Swithin's-Alley by the Royal Exchange, 1720.) http://library.st-andrews.ac.uk/record=b2413658~S1
